-- Nigeria's forex reserves down 3 percent in two weeks on cbank naira support 
-- 
-- Mon Nov 17, 2014 09:07AM EST
-- None



LAGOS, Nov 17 (Reuters) - Nigeria's foreign exchange reserves <NGFXR=ECI> fell 3 percent in two weeks to $37.59 billion by Nov. 13, as the central bank stepped up support for the ailing naira <NGN=D1> currency.

Data published by the central bank on Monday showed the reserves were at $38.76 billion on October 29.